<DIV1 TYPE="poem">
<PB REF="039314_0007_1013FBFF628F59E0">
<HEAD>Precepts for Children.</HEAD>
<LG>
<L>TO learn to Read good Child, give heed,</L>
<L>For 'tis a precious thing:</L>
<L>What may compare, with Learning rare?</L>
<L>From hence doth Virtue &s;piring.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="2">
<HEAD>2.</HEAD>
<L>In time of Grief, i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> yeilds Relief;</L>
<L>Yea&punc; in Adver&s;ity</L>
<L>'Twill cheerful make, when Friends for&s;ake,</L>
<L>And when dear Parents dye.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="3">
<HEAD>3.</HEAD>
<L>When Foes annoy&punc; 'twill yeild thee Joy&punc;</L>
<L>With much Delight and Plea&s;ure:</L>
<L>If Poor thou be, this will to the<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></L>
<L>Exceed all earthly Trea&s;ure.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="4">
<HEAD>4.</HEAD>
<L>Though others have, and Riches crave,</L>
<L>&V;nto their hearts de&s;ire.</L>
<L>It may decay, and fly away,</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e c<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n&s;u<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">'d by <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ire:</L>
</LG>
<LG N="5">
<HEAD>5.</HEAD>
<L>Thy Portion's &s;ure, and will endure&punc;</L>
<L>Nought can undo that youth</L>
<L>Whom God doth learn, for to di&s;cern</L>
<L>The worth of &s;acred Truth.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="6">
<HEAD>6.</HEAD>
<L>Take therefore care Learning's more ra<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"></L>
<L>Than Chains of pure&s;t Gold;</L>
<L>Look, look about and find it out,</L>
<L>Its worth cannot be told,</L>
</LG>
<LG N="7">
<PB REF="039314_0008_1013FC46D9225B50">
<HEAD>7.</HEAD>
<L><HI>Con&s;onants</HI> know, and <HI>Vowels</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">,</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ay, learn r<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">tly to Spell;</L>
<L>Be not a Fool, but go to School,</L>
<L>Till thou read <HI>Engli&s;h</HI> well;</L>
</LG>
<LG N="8">
<HEAD>8&middot;</HEAD>
<L>Yet <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ere, but learn to fear</L>
<L>The Ble&s;&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">d GOD of Truth;</L>
<L>O under&s;tand tis <HI>Gods</HI> Command</L>
<L>To &s;erve him in thy Yo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="9">
<HEAD>9.</HEAD>
<L>Learn to deny the Company</L>
<L>Of Children who are vile,</L>
<L>That Lye and Swear, &s;o wicked are,</L>
<L>As good Men to revile,</L>
</LG>
<LG N="10">
<HEAD>10</HEAD>
<L>O learn to know what filth doth flow</L>
<L>From every poi&s;onous Evil,</L>
<L>And look within, to find out Sin,</L>
<L>Tis wor&s;er than the Devil.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="11">
<HEAD>11&middot;</HEAD>
<L>What <HI>Adam's</HI> Fall htah brought on all,</L>
<L>His whole Po&s;terity&punc;</L>
<L>Strive to find out, then without doubt</L>
<L>To <HI>Je&s;us</HI> thou will fly.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="12">
<HEAD>12.</HEAD>
<L>For fit releif, vnder thy Grief,</L>
<L>On him do thou depend;</L>
<L>And he will <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ear, and will appear</L>
<L>To &s;ave thee in the end.</L>
</LG>
